                   Full Committee Tax Markups and Meetings

     * December 15, 2000
          + House passed H.R. 3594, the "Installment Tax Correction Act of
            2000."   The bill was referred to the Committee but was not
            marked up. P.L. 106-573
          + House passed the conference report H. Rept. 106-1033, to
            accompany H.R. 4557, the "Consolidated Appropriations Act,
            2001," which incorporated the text of H.R. 5662, the
            "Community Renewal Tax Relief Act of 2000," and H.R. 5661, the
            "Medicare, Medicaid and SCHIP Benefits Improvement and
            Protection Act of 2000."  P.L. 106-554.
     * October 26, 2000
          + House passed the conference report (H. Rept. 106-1004), to
            accompany H.R. 2614, the "Enactment of Certain Small Business,
            Health, Tax, and Minimum Wage Provisions, " which included the
            provisions of H.R. 5542, the "Taxpayer Relief Act," and H.R.
            5543, the "Medicare, Medicaid, and SCHIP Benefits Improvement
            and Protection Act."  These bills,  H.R. 5542 and H.R. 5543,
            were referred to the Committee but were not marked up.
     * September 26, 2000
          + House passed H.R. 5117, the "Missing Children Tax Fairness Act
            of 2000."  The bill was referred to the Committee but was not
            marked up.  See H.R. 2614 above for further action.
     * September 14, 2000
          + Markup of H.R. 5173, the "Debt Relief Lock-box Reconciliation
            Act for Fiscal Year 2001" -- Action Release, H. Rept. 106-862,
            Part 1.  H.R. 5203 subsequently passed the House with the text
            of H.R. 5173, and H.R. 1102, on September 29, 2000.
     * July 27, 2000
          + Markup of H.R. 4986, the "FSC Repeal and Extraterritorial
            Income Exclusion  Act of 2000" -- Action Release, H. Rept.
            106-845, P.L. 106-519
     * July 25, 2000
          + House passed H.R. 4923, the "Community Renewal and New Markets
            Act of 2000."  The bill was referred to the Committee but was
            not marked up.
     * July 19, 2000
          + Markup of H.R. 4865, the "Social Security Benefits Tax Relief
            Act of 2000" -- Action Release, H. Rept. 106-780
     * July 18, 2000
          + House passed H.R. 4866, the "Debt Relief Reconciliation Act
            for Fiscal Year 2001."  The bill was referred to the Committee
            but was not marked up.
     * July 13, 2000
          + Markup of H.R. 4843, the "Comprehensive Retirement Security
            and Pension Reform Act of 2000" -- Action Release,  H. Rept.
            106-753.  H.R. 1102 subsequently passed the House on July 19,
            2000, with the text of H.R. 4843.  Also see H.R. 5203 for
            additional action.
     * July 12, 2000
          + House passed conference report (H. Rept. 106-765) to accompany
            H.R. 4810, the "Marriage Tax Relief Reconciliation Act of
            2000."   The bill was referred to the Committee but was not
            marked up.   Presidential veto on August 5, 2000.
     * June 22, 2000
          + Markup of H.R. 4717, the "Full and Fair Political Activity
            Disclosure Act of 2000. " --  Action Release, H. Rept.
            106-702, subsequently H.R. 4762, passed House on June 28 and
            the Senate on June 29, 2000, and signed into law July 1, 2000,
            P.L. 106-230.
     * June 8, 2000
          + Markup of H.R. 4601, the "Debt Reduction Reconciliation Act of
            2000" --  Action Release, H. Rept. 106-673, Pt. 1
     * May 25, 2000
          + Markup of H.R 8, the "Death Tax Elimination Act of 2000" --
            Action Release, H. Rept. 106-651.  Presidential veto August
            31, 2000.
     * May 17, 2000
          + Markup of H.R. 3916, a bill to amend the Internal Revenue Code
            of 1986 to repeal the excise tax on telephone and other
            communication services -- Action Release, H. Rept. 106-631
     * April 13, 2000
          + House passed H.R.  4199, the "Date Certain Tax Code
            Replacement Act."  The bill was referred to the Committee but
            was not marked up.
     * April 5, 2000
          + Markup of H.R 4163, the "Taxpayer Bill of Rights 2000" --
            Action Release, H. Rept. 106-566
     * March 22, 2000
          + Markup of H.R 7, the "Education Savings and School Excellence
            Act of 2000" -- Action Release, H. Rept. 106-546
     * February 2, 2000
          + Markup of H.R. 6, the "Marriage Tax Penalty Relief of 2000" --
            Action Release, H. Rept. 106-493.   For further action, see
            H.R. 4810 above.
     * November 9, 1999
          + Markup of H.R. 3081, the "Wage and Employment Growth Act of
            1999" -- Action Release, H. Rept. 106-467, Part 1
     * October 14, 1999
          + Markup of H.R. 3070, the "Ticket to Work and Work Incentives
            Improvement Act of 1999" -- Action Release, H. Rept. 106-393,
            Pt. 1, Conference Report H. Rept. 106-478 - (H.R. 1180),
            Including Certain Expiring Tax Provisions, Conference Action
            Release, P.L. 106-170
     * September 27, 1999
          + Markup of H.R. 2923, a bill to amend the Internal Revenue Code
            of 1986 to extend expiring provisions, to fully allow
            nonrefundable personal credits against regular tax liability
            -- Action Release, H. Rept. 106-344, Conference Report Rept.
            106-478 (H.R. 1180), Including Certain Expiring Tax
            Provisions, Conference Action Release, P.L. 106-170
     * July 13 & 14, 1999
          + Markup of H.R. 2488, the "Financial Freedom Act of 1999" --
            Action Release, Floor Action Release, H. Rept. 106-238,
            Conference Report H. Rept. 106-289, Overview of Conference
            (JCX-60-99), Summary of the Revenue Provisions of the
            Conference Agreement on H.R. 2488, the "Taxpayer Refund and
            Relief Act of 1999" (JCX-63-99).  Presidential veto on
            September 23, 1999.
     * April 13, 1999
          + Markup of H.R. 1376, a bill to extend tax relief for personnel
            involved in Operation Allied Force-- Action Release, H. Rept.
            106-90, P.L. 106-21
     * February 11, 1999
          + Markup of H.R. 416, the "Federal Retirement Coverage
            Corrections Act " -- Action Release. H. Rept. 106-29, Pt. 2
